    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5daf7315_f0f1385d",
        "filename": "include/codec/SkCodec.h",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 398,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-27T14:50:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We use const SkPixmap to disallow changing the configuration of the pixmap (image info, where it points) but the constness doesn\u0027t apply to the pixel data in the pixmap. This is the same. Removing const here would allow the client to reconfigure the SkYUVAPixmaps, which we definitely don\u0027t want. The only alternative would be to pass by value.\n\nIt\u0027s like const std::unique_ptr\u003cT\u003e\u0026 vs std::unique_ptr\u003cconst T\u003e\u0026 except we don\u0027t have an SkConstPixmap equivalent to the latter.",
      "parentUuid": "c09171eb_4c6e9e5a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 398,
        "startChar": 25,
        "endLine": 398,
        "endChar": 46
      },
      "revId": "3ab92c4cd8a6c45ced1f133bb240797a2c76fc3b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
